This section merges backend architectural insights from Phase 2 and the Full Audit.

5.1 ORPC/Next.js Backend Pattern

The backend uses typed ORPC procedures grouped by access level:

Public Procedures (publicProcedure)

Accessible without authentication.

Used for shared read-only data.

Protected Procedures (protectedProcedure)

Requires authentication.

Used for private user operations.

Admin Procedures (adminProcedure)

Requires elevated role (admin or super_admin).

Used for admin-only endpoints.

Procedure Structure

Most procedures follow the pattern:

input validation

permission verification

database query

optional side effects (emails, events)

return typed response

5.2 Public vs Protected vs Admin Procedure Types
Public

Limited scope

Often used for metadata, not user-specific information

Protected

Used for tasks like:

updating user profile

fetching user subscriptions

accessing user content

Admin

Used for tasks like:

listing users

impersonation

banning/unbanning

changing user roles

fetching subscription details

interacting with affiliate data

Only this procedure type is allowed in the admin dashboard’s backend.

